## 5. Domain Segmentation

### 5.1 Seven operational domains
| # | Domain                     | Owner / responsible MCP             | Owner / responsible engine module                                |
|---|----------------------------|-------------------------------------|------------------------------------------------------------------|
| 1 | Runtime analysis           | Chrome DevTools                     | `lib/scroll/`, `lib/webgl/`, browser runtime                     |
| 2 | Architectural reasoning    | Sequential Thinking + main agent    | `lib/chapters/`, `lib/density/`, `lib/transitions/`              |
| 3 | Deployment systems         | Vercel                              | `next.config.*`, CI/CD                                           |
| 4 | Backend / narrative data   | Supabase                            | `content/`, future `lib/data/`                                   |
| 5 | Cinematic systems          | (no MCP; main agent + operator)     | `lib/motion/`, `lib/atmosphere/`, `lib/irregularity/`, `lib/sound/` |
| 6 | Performance systems        | Chrome DevTools (diagnostic only)   | `performance-system.mdc`, `lib/webgl/`, asset pipeline           |
| 7 | Continuity systems         | (no MCP; main agent + operator)     | `/docs/`, `.rules/`, `docs/changelogs/`                          |

### 5.2 Cross-domain rule
**No MCP may operate outside its assigned domain without escalation.**

Examples of forbidden cross-domain operations:
- ❌ Chrome DevTools recommends a chapter restructure (cinematic system — not its domain).
- ❌ Context7 fetches "best practices" for animation choreography (cinematic system — locked vocabulary, not external).
- ❌ Sequential Thinking reasons about deployment strategies (deployment system — Vercel + operator).
- ❌ Supabase suggests UI changes for a contact form (cinematic system — frontend code, not data layer).
- ❌ Vercel suggests changing motion durations to "improve INP" (cinematic system — performance budget is bounded by `performance-system.mdc`, not optimized away).

If a cross-domain suggestion arises, the main agent **does not act on it**; the suggestion is logged as out-of-scope and escalated to the operator if material.

### 5.3 Cinematic systems are MCP-untouchable
Domain 5 (Cinematic systems) and Domain 7 (Continuity systems) have **no MCP owner by design**. These domains are governed by:
- Operator creative direction.
- The 17 `.mdc` rules.
- The 13 `/docs/` files (including this ruleset).
- The 6 HTML canon files.

No MCP may write into these domains. Any MCP-originated suggestion to alter cinematic or continuity systems is reviewed by the operator and applied (or rejected) through standard PR flow with a `docs:` or `rule:` prefix.

