## 9. Failure Modes

### 9.1 Orchestration failure states

| State                       | Symptoms                                                                 | Cause                                                       | Recovery protocol                                                                                                            | Escalation                |
|-----------------------------|--------------------------------------------------------------------------|-------------------------------------------------------------|------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|---------------------------|
| **Continuity corruption**   | `MASTER_STATE.md` disagrees with reality; missing changelog for shipped change | Session ended without closing protocol                      | Reconstruct missed update before any new code work (per `DEVELOPMENT_GUIDELINES.md §12.5.5`); generate retroactive changelog | Operator notified         |
| **Agent collision**         | Two agents (main + subagent) modify the same file in the same session    | Subagent given write authority outside its slice            | Revert subagent changes; restrict subagent to read-only; main agent re-implements                                            | Operator if recurring     |
| **Governance drift**        | Implementation diverges from `.rules/` over multiple sessions             | Orchestration audits skipped; rules not consulted           | Half-day continuity recalibration (per `CHAT_CONTINUITY_WORKFLOW.md §11`); audit all sessions since last clean state         | Operator schedules        |
| **Memory desynchronization**| `/docs/` and `.rules/` reference removed files; cross-doc links broken    | `/docs/` updates without rule updates (or vice versa)       | Run `DEVELOPMENT_GUIDELINES.md §13` matrix; update all dependent docs in a single `docs:` PR                                | Operator approves PR      |
| **Runtime instability**     | Production performance regression; chapter atmosphere flickers; WebGL context loss | L3 deploy without performance verification; missed CI gate  | Vercel rollback (immediate); root-cause analysis; fix-forward in next deploy with performance trace as PR artifact           | Operator notified on prod |
| **MCP authority breach**    | An MCP wrote to a forbidden domain (e.g., L2 modified governance)        | Subagent / MCP not bounded; escalation rule not enforced    | Revert the change; identify the un-bounded invocation; tighten the guard; log incident                                       | Operator + audit          |
| **Reasoning loop**          | Sequential Thinking exceeds 7 steps; recursive MCP calls                 | Task scope too large; mode mismatch (LIGHTWEIGHT vs ARCHITECTURE) | Halt the chain; restart session with correct mode                                                                            | Main agent decides        |
| **Context flooding**        | > 30k tokens of project context loaded; agent reasoning degrades          | Continuity mode mis-selected; documents loaded eagerly      | Restart session; load on-demand only the slice the task requires (`CHAT_CONTINUITY_WORKFLOW.md §5`)                          | Self-correct              |

### 9.2 Failure mode detection
Continuous detection happens through:
- **Closing protocol** (per `DEVELOPMENT_GUIDELINES.md §12.5`) — catches missed updates.
- **Monthly continuity audit** (per `CHAT_CONTINUITY_WORKFLOW.md §11`) — catches drift.
- **CI gates** (per `DEVELOPMENT_GUIDELINES.md §14.2`) — catches performance + a11y regressions.
- **PR review checklist** (per `DEVELOPMENT_GUIDELINES.md §4.2`) — catches per-change violations.

